Geraldine Jones, 36, of Gary, Indiana, charged with murder, kidnapping and criminal confinement in the death of Samantha Fleming . 
  Fleming and her three-week old baby went missing from her home in Anderson on April 5 . 
  Police found her body stabbed, wrapped in plastic and soaked in bleach in Jones' home . 
  Jones told police she was a child-welfare worker and told Fleming she needed to attend a hearing . 
  She is being treated in Texas for depression . 
  Fleming was lured to her home by Jones and her baby was stolen . 
 